Mimir coding engine
====================

The file `editblock.py` in this package contains code adapted from Aider
(https://github.com/aider-ai/aider), specifically the module-level, I/O-free functions of
`aider/coders/editblock_coder.py` (SEARCH/REPLACE block parsing and fault-tolerant application).

Aider is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
Copyright (c) Aider AI and contributors.

Modifications for Mimir:
  * Removed all `aider.*` imports (utils, dump, base_coder, editblock_prompts); none were used by the
    vendored functions.
  * `do_replace()` no longer performs filesystem I/O (the original `Path.touch()` for new files was
    removed) — it is now a pure string→string transform. File reads/writes happen only through Mimir's
    broker primitives (project_read_scoped / project_write_out).
  * Added `apply_edit()`, a pure convenience wrapper.

